content:
To add controls for a mobile device, we will create four buttons for up, down, left, and right movements. Then, we'll add event listeners to these buttons to handle player movement. Follow these steps:

1. Update the HTML file (index.html) to add mobile controls:
```html
<!-- Add the following div below the #difficulty-control div -->

<div id="mobile-controls">
  <button id="up-btn">↑</button>
  <button id="left-btn">←</button>
  <button id="right-btn">→</button>
  <button id="down-btn">↓</button>
</div>
```
1. Update the JavaScript file (game.js) to add event listeners for mobile controls:
```javascript
// Add the following code at the bottom of the game.js file

document.getElementById('up-btn').addEventListener('click', () => movePlayer(0, -1));
document.getElementById('left-btn').addEventListener('click', () => movePlayer(-1, 0));
document.getElementById('right-btn').addEventListener('click', () => movePlayer(1, 0));
document.getElementById('down-btn').addEventListener('click', () => movePlayer(0, 1));
```
